The Download Archive page contains all previous releases but does not contain the latest release. If this page contained all releases, including latest, it would be a single source to find all of the versions.

Customer Use Case:

{quote}
With the new JIRA and Bitbucket releases the download pages do not show the version. I can get the version by hovering over the download button and looking at the URL but... It would be nice to have a single place to see the latest release versions of Atlassian Software.
{quote}

In start-bitbucket.sh the command for launching Bitbucket as another user looks like this:
{code}
$sucmd -l $BITBUCKET_USER -c "cd $(pwd);$PRGDIR/catalina.sh run $@"
{code}

In stop-bitbucket.sh it looks like this:
{code}
$sucmd -m $BITBUCKET_USER -c "$PRGDIR/shutdown.sh 60 -force $@"
{code}

By using -m instead of -l in stop-bitbucket.sh, shutdown.sh won't get the environment of BITBUCKET_USER and will therefore fail. Right now the workaround is having to define everything in setenv.sh.

